= SDL_SetWindowDisplayMode =
Use this function to set the display mode used when a fullscreen window is visible on the currently selected display. __By default the window's dimensions and the desktop format and refresh rate are used.__


== Syntax ==
```c++
int SDL_SetWindowDisplayMode(SDL_Window*            window,
                             const SDL_DisplayMode* mode)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''window'''
|the type used to identify the window
|-
|'''mode'''
|a pointer to the [[SDL_DisplayMode]] to use, or NULL for the default mode
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns 0 on success or -1 if setting the display mode failed; call [[SDL_GetError]]() for more information.

